-style-preset: corporate-premium

CONTEXT: Official Corporate Identity Presentation Slides.

VISUAL STYLE: Emotional, inspiring, and authentic. Ultra-minimalist, high-end automotive aesthetic. Open and spacious.

BACKGROUND: Solid Blue (matching the exact color of the uploaded patch). NO gradients, NO textures, just flat solid blue.

LAYOUT & COMPOSITION:
• ⁠FORMAT: 16:9
• ⁠GRID: Strict grid alignment. Use thin white vertical lines (hairlines) to visually separate columns.
• ⁠NEGATIVE SPACE: Use significant negative space. Elements must "float" directly on the blue background.
• ⁠PROHIBITED: STRICTLY NO CONTAINERS (no white boxes, no grey frames behind text). NO OVERLAPS (text and images must not overlap). NO SLANTED EDGES (90-degree alignment only).

COLOR PALETTE:
• ⁠Primary Text: Pure White (#FFFFFF).
• ⁠Accent: Pure White (#FFFFFF) or contrasting light grey. Use sparingly for highlights, active timeline segments, or focus points.
• ⁠Secondary: Cool functional Greys (Hex #B3B3B3 to #4C4C4C) for diagrams or inactive elements.

TYPOGRAPHY RULES:
• ⁠Style: Geometric Sans-serif, extended width, clean lines. Headlines bold, body normal. High contrast.
• ⁠Casing: Sentence case or Title case. NEVER USE ALL-CAPS (Uppercasing is strictly forbidden).

GRAPHIC ELEMENTS:
• ⁠List Elements: Bullet points must be small White chevrons/arrowheads (›).

ILUSTRATIONS:
• ⁠STYLE DEFINITION: Corporate Illustration Style based on "Tape Drawing".
• ⁠VISUAL ESTETIC: Ultra-minimalist, technical but fluid line art.
• ⁠LINEWORK QUALITY:
-- Constant stroke width (Monoline): Lines must look like laid tape – consistent thickness, no calligraphy effects (thin/thick variation).
-- Dynamic Flow: Lines should suggest movement and precision. Long, sweeping curves.
-- No Fills: Strictly outlines only. No solid shapes, no shading, no 3D effects.
• ⁠COLOR PALETTE:
-- Lines: Pure White (#FFFFFF).
-- Accent: Use Pure White (#FFFFFF) very sparingly for a single active element or direction indicator.
• ⁠COMPOSITION:
-- Abstract & Simple: Reduce complex objects (cars, hands, clouds) to their absolute essential contours.
-- Open Shapes: Lines do not always need to close. Use negative space.
-- 2D Flat: Strictly two-dimensional.
